r life brings together a range of international high profile scholars to develop a more sophisticated, analytical and empirical understanding of class dynamics in later life. It will be of major interest to students and researchers examining the implications of global ageing, and will appeal to scholars concerned with the development of a more critical and engaged gerontology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aOlder peoplexEconomic conditions. 0aOlder peoplexSocial conditions. 0aSocial classes. 0aSocial perception in old age. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gerontology.2bisacsh1 aBottero, Wendy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFormosa, Marvin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFormosa, Marvin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHafford-Letchfield, Trish, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggs, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHiggs, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHyde, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Ian Rees, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopes, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStorelli, Elizangela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVictor, Christina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliamson, John B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backl